Package com.sanyavertolet.interview.data.value

Class Value

java.lang.Object
com.sanyavertolet.interview.data.value.Value
Direct Known Subclasses:
BooleanValue, DoubleValue, IntegerValue, IterableValue, StringValue
public abstract sealed class Value extends Object permits BooleanValue, DoubleValue, StringValue, IntegerValue, IterableValue
An abstract sealed class representing a value that can be used in expressions and evaluated. The Value class provides basic arithmetic and comparison operations, and it permits specific subclasses such as BooleanValue, DoubleValue, StringValue, IntegerValue, and IterableValue.

Subclasses of Value are expected to implement these operations where appropriate. By default, most operations will throw a ValueCastException if they are not supported by the specific type of value.

    • parse

      public static Value parse(String valueText)
      Parses a string to determine its corresponding Value type. The method attempts to parse the string as a boolean, then as an integer, and finally as a double. If none of these conversions are successful, the string is treated as a StringValue.
      Parameters:
      valueText - the string representation of the value to be parsed.
      Returns:
      a Value instance corresponding to the parsed string.
